DUTSE – About 4,000 vulnerable wom­en drawn from 20 Local Gov­ernment Areas of Jigawa State have secured N20,000 each from the federal gov­ernment social investment scheme under Federal Min­istry for Humanitarian Af­fairs, Disaster Management and Social Development. The Minister, Hajiya Sadiya Umar Farouk who flagged-off the grant in Du­tse, explained that the pro­gramme covers at least 4,000 vulnerable women from 20 LGAs. Farouk, represented by the permanent secretary in the ministry, Alhaji Bashir Nuhu Alkali said about 120,000 people would benefit nationwide from the exercise which was an ongoing social investment programme under the Fed­eral government. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Alhaji Bashir Nuhu not­ed that a team of tradition­al leaders, religious leaders, heads of associations and community organisations which include women were selected to spearhead the se­lection process of vulnera­ble women.